      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"1. SHARNI'S SECRET turned in a plain effort last time when seventh at this track over 435m behind Paw Kramer (25.18) in a Grade 5. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. 2. NIGHT SHARID is a last start placegetter in Grade 5 company, jumping from this box and finishing a 4 length third over 450m at Shepparton. Has a very honest record from this same draw, including a win and three minors. Has the ability and can measure up. 7. DR. AZURE was in traffic and took a tumble last time at Sandown but was placed in a Grade 5 the start prior. Rates a key player and gets chance to atone. 6. HOLLY ROSE has ability and finds the right scenario to bounce back.\",\"runners\":[1,2,6],\"exclusive\":false}",
